A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Environment – Interjurisdictional Watersheds – Flood Management
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the Department of the Environment to designate certain
4 watersheds and all their headwaters and tributaries as interjurisdictional flood
5 hazard watersheds; and generally relating to interjurisdictional watersheds and
6 flood management.
7 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
8 Article – Environment
9 Section 5–801 and 5–803(d) and (e)
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2013 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Environment
15 5–801.
16 (a) In this subtitle the following terms have the meanings indicated.
17 (b) “Area of nontidal inundation” means an area within the State which is subject
18 to inundation caused predominately by accumulated surface runoff or excess rainfall runoff,
19 or both.
20 (c) “Area of tidal inundation” means an area within the State which is subject to
21 inundation caused predominately by tides or wind–driven waters, or both.
22 (d) “Department” means the Department of the Environment.
